%% DALP API gateway request lifecycle.
%% Shows full request path: authentication, authorization, execution, response.
%% Use in API architecture, security, integration, and developer experience sections.
%% Evaluator focus: security-first design, RBAC enforcement, audit logging, error handling.
%%{init: {
  "theme": "base",
  "themeVariables": {"fontFamily": "Figtree, Inter, Arial, sans-serif", "fontSize": "15px", "textColor": "#1A1A2E", "lineColor": "#6B7280", "background": "#FFFFFF"},
  "sequence": {"mirrorActors": false, "showSequenceNumbers": false, "diagramMarginX": 40, "diagramMarginY": 20, "messageMargin": 28, "boxMargin": 12, "actorMargin": 40, "width": 170, "height": 64},
  "securityLevel": "loose"
}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant APP as Client Application
    participant GW as API Gateway
    participant AUTH as Auth Service<br/>(JWT + OIDC)
    participant RBAC as AccessManager<br/>(RBAC / ABAC)
    participant UAPI as Unified API
    participant EE as Execution Engine
    participant LOG as Audit Log
    participant BC as Blockchain

    APP->>GW: API request (Bearer token)
    GW->>GW: Rate limit check

    alt Rate limit exceeded
        GW-->>APP: 429 Too Many Requests
    end

    GW->>AUTH: Validate JWT
    AUTH->>AUTH: Verify signature + expiry
    AUTH-->>GW: Token valid (tenant, roles, scopes)

    GW->>RBAC: Authorize action
    RBAC->>RBAC: Evaluate RBAC + ABAC policies
    RBAC-->>GW: Authorization decision

    alt Unauthorized
        RBAC-->>GW: 403 Forbidden
        GW->>LOG: Log denied request
        GW-->>APP: 403 Forbidden
    end

    GW->>UAPI: Forward authorized request
    GW->>LOG: Log request metadata
    UAPI->>EE: Execute operation

    alt Write operation (transaction)
        EE->>BC: Submit transaction
        BC-->>EE: Transaction receipt
        EE-->>UAPI: Execution result
        UAPI->>LOG: Log operation outcome
        UAPI-->>GW: 200 Success + result
        GW-->>APP: Response payload
    else Read operation (query)
        EE-->>UAPI: Query result
        UAPI-->>GW: 200 Success + data
        GW-->>APP: Response payload
    else Execution error
        EE-->>UAPI: Error details
        UAPI->>LOG: Log error
        UAPI-->>GW: 4xx/5xx Error
        GW-->>APP: Error response
    end

    Note over APP,GW: [CLIENT: Configure OIDC provider, allowed scopes, and rate limit tiers here]
